<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8" standalone="yes"?><rss version="2.0" xmlns:atom="http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom"><channel><title>Classcastexception on ErrorCode — Error Code Reference &amp; Solutions</title><link>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/tags/classcastexception/</link><description>Recent content in Classcastexception on ErrorCode — Error Code Reference &amp; Solutions</description><generator>Hugo</generator><language>en</language><atom:link href="https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/tags/classcastexception/index.xml" rel="self" type="application/rss+xml"/><item><title>[Solution] Java ClassCastException: Cannot Be Cast To Fix</title><link>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/java/classcast-error/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/java/classcast-error/</guid><description>&lt;h1 id="classcastexception-cannot-be-cast-to"&gt;ClassCastException: Cannot Be Cast To&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;A &lt;code&gt;ClassCastException&lt;/code&gt; is thrown when you attempt to cast an object to a type it is not an instance of at runtime. Despite Java&amp;rsquo;s compile-time type checking, casts on &lt;code&gt;Object&lt;/code&gt; references, raw collections, and generic type erasure can produce invalid casts that only fail at runtime.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id="description"&gt;Description&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Java enforces type safety at compile time, but some casts bypass the compiler and are validated at runtime. When the actual object type doesn&amp;rsquo;t match the target type, the JVM throws &lt;code&gt;ClassCastException&lt;/code&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;</description></item><item><title>[Solution] Kotlin ClassCastException — Type Cast Failed Fix</title><link>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/kotlin/typecast-kotlin/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/kotlin/typecast-kotlin/</guid><description>&lt;h1 id="classcastexception--type-cast-failed"&gt;ClassCastException — Type Cast Failed&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;A &lt;code&gt;ClassCastException&lt;/code&gt; occurs when you attempt to cast an object to a type it doesn&amp;rsquo;t belong to.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id="description"&gt;Description&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Kotlin uses &lt;code&gt;as&lt;/code&gt; for explicit type casts. If the object isn&amp;rsquo;t of the target type, the cast fails. Kotlin&amp;rsquo;s &lt;code&gt;is&lt;/code&gt; check and safe cast &lt;code&gt;as?&lt;/code&gt; help prevent these errors.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Common causes:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Unsafe downcast&lt;/strong&gt; — casting to incorrect subtype&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Java generic erasure&lt;/strong&gt; — runtime type information lost&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Wrong collection type&lt;/strong&gt; — casting collection elements&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Interface implementation&lt;/strong&gt; — casting to wrong interface&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h2 id="common-causes"&gt;Common Causes&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-kotlin" data-lang="kotlin"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// Cause 1: Unsafe downcast
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;open&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;class&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;Animal&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;class&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;Dog&lt;/span&gt; : Animal()
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;class&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;Cat&lt;/span&gt; : Animal()
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;val&lt;/span&gt; animal: Animal = Cat()
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;val&lt;/span&gt; dog = animal &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;as&lt;/span&gt; Dog &lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// ClassCastException
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// Cause 2: Java generic erasure
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;val&lt;/span&gt; list: List&amp;lt;Any&amp;gt; = listOf(&lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;a&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;, &lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;b&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;, &lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;c&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;)
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;val&lt;/span&gt; strings = list &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;as&lt;/span&gt; List&amp;lt;String&amp;gt; &lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// May throw ClassCastException
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// Cause 3: Wrong collection type
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;val&lt;/span&gt; mixed: List&amp;lt;Any&amp;gt; = listOf(&lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;1&lt;/span&gt;, &lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;two&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;, &lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;3.0&lt;/span&gt;)
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;val&lt;/span&gt; first = mixed[&lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;0&lt;/span&gt;] &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;as&lt;/span&gt; String &lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// ClassCastException
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// Cause 4: Interface cast
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;val&lt;/span&gt; map = HashMap&amp;lt;String, Int&amp;gt;()
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;val&lt;/span&gt; mutableMap = map &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;as&lt;/span&gt; MutableMap&amp;lt;String, Int&amp;gt; &lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// Works, but risky
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h2 id="how-to-fix"&gt;How to Fix&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;h3 id="fix-1-use-safe-cast-as"&gt;Fix 1: Use safe cast &lt;code&gt;as?&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-kotlin" data-lang="kotlin"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// Wrong
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;val&lt;/span&gt; animal: Animal = Cat()
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;val&lt;/span&gt; dog = animal &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;as&lt;/span&gt; Dog &lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// ClassCastException
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// Correct
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;val&lt;/span&gt; dog = animal &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;as&lt;/span&gt;? Dog
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;dog&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;?.&lt;/span&gt;bark() &lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// Safe, dog is null if cast fails
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h3 id="fix-2-use-is-check"&gt;Fix 2: Use &lt;code&gt;is&lt;/code&gt; check&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-kotlin" data-lang="kotlin"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// Wrong
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;val&lt;/span&gt; animal: Animal = Cat()
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;val&lt;/span&gt; dog = animal &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;as&lt;/span&gt; Dog &lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// ClassCastException
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// Correct
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;if&lt;/span&gt; (animal &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;is&lt;/span&gt; Dog) {
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; animal.bark()
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;}
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h3 id="fix-3-use-when-for-multiple-types"&gt;Fix 3: Use &lt;code&gt;when&lt;/code&gt; for multiple types&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-kotlin" data-lang="kotlin"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// Wrong
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;val&lt;/span&gt; animal: Animal = Cat()
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;val&lt;/span&gt; dog = animal &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;as&lt;/span&gt; Dog &lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// ClassCastException
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// Correct
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;when&lt;/span&gt; (animal) {
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;is&lt;/span&gt; Dog &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;-&amp;gt;&lt;/span&gt; animal.bark()
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;is&lt;/span&gt; Cat &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;-&amp;gt;&lt;/span&gt; animal.meow()
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;else&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;-&amp;gt;&lt;/span&gt; println(&lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;Unknown animal&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;)
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;}
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h3 id="fix-4-filter-collection-elements"&gt;Fix 4: Filter collection elements&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-kotlin" data-lang="kotlin"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// Wrong
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;val&lt;/span&gt; mixed: List&amp;lt;Any&amp;gt; = listOf(&lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;1&lt;/span&gt;, &lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;two&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;, &lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;3.0&lt;/span&gt;)
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;val&lt;/span&gt; first = mixed[&lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;0&lt;/span&gt;] &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;as&lt;/span&gt; String &lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// ClassCastException
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// Correct
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;val&lt;/span&gt; strings = mixed.filterIsInstance&amp;lt;String&amp;gt;()
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h2 id="examples"&gt;Examples&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-kotlin" data-lang="kotlin"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// Example 1: Safe casting with smart cast
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;fun&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;process&lt;/span&gt;(&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;value&lt;/span&gt;: Any) {
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;when&lt;/span&gt; (&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;value&lt;/span&gt;) {
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;is&lt;/span&gt; String &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;-&amp;gt;&lt;/span&gt; println(&lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;String: &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;$value&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;)
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;is&lt;/span&gt; Int &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;-&amp;gt;&lt;/span&gt; println(&lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;Int: &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;$value&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;)
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;is&lt;/span&gt; Double &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;-&amp;gt;&lt;/span&gt; println(&lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;Double: &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;$value&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;)
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;else&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;-&amp;gt;&lt;/span&gt; println(&lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;Unknown type&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;)
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; }
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;}
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// Example 2: Safe collection casting
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;val&lt;/span&gt; data: List&amp;lt;Any&amp;gt; = listOf(&lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;1&lt;/span&gt;, &lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;hello&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;, &lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;3.0&lt;/span&gt;)
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;val&lt;/span&gt; strings = &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;data&lt;/span&gt;.filterIsInstance&amp;lt;String&amp;gt;()
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;val&lt;/span&gt; ints = &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;data&lt;/span&gt;.filterIsInstance&amp;lt;Int&amp;gt;()
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h2 id="related-errors"&gt;Related Errors&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/kotlin/nullpointer-kotlin/"&gt;NullPointerException&lt;/a&gt; — null dereference&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/kotlin/illegal-argument/"&gt;IllegalArgumentException&lt;/a&gt; — invalid argument&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/kotlin/unsupported-operation/"&gt;UnsupportedOperationException&lt;/a&gt; — unsupported operation&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;</description></item><item><title>[Solution] Kotlin ClassCastException — Type Cast Fix</title><link>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/kotlin/class-cast/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/kotlin/class-cast/</guid><description>&lt;h1 id="classcastexception--type-cast-fix"&gt;ClassCastException — Type Cast Fix&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;A &lt;code&gt;ClassCastException&lt;/code&gt; is thrown when you attempt to cast an object to a type that it is not an instance of. This commonly occurs with unsafe casts using the &lt;code&gt;as&lt;/code&gt; operator.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id="description"&gt;Description&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Kotlin&amp;rsquo;s &lt;code&gt;as&lt;/code&gt; operator performs an unchecked cast at runtime. If the object is not an instance of the target type, the cast fails with &lt;code&gt;ClassCastException&lt;/code&gt;. This is common when working with generic types, Java interop, or heterogeneous collections.&lt;/p&gt;</description></item><item><title>ClassCastException</title><link>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/groovy/cast-error/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/groovy/cast-error/</guid><description>&lt;h2 id="what-this-error-means"&gt;What This Error Means&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;A &lt;code&gt;ClassCastException&lt;/code&gt; is thrown when you try to cast an object to a type that it isn&amp;rsquo;t compatible with. Groovy performs runtime type checking for explicit casts using the &lt;code&gt;as&lt;/code&gt; keyword.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id="common-causes"&gt;Common Causes&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Casting incompatible types&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Assumptions about return types from methods&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Generic type erasure causing wrong assumptions&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Interoperating with Java collections&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h2 id="how-to-fix"&gt;How to Fix&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-groovy" data-lang="groovy"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// WRONG: Invalid cast
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;def&lt;/span&gt; x &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;hello&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;def&lt;/span&gt; n &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; x &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;as&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;int&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// ClassCastException
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// CORRECT: Check type before casting
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;def&lt;/span&gt; x &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;hello&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;if&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;(&lt;/span&gt;x &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;instanceof&lt;/span&gt; Integer&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;)&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;{&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;def&lt;/span&gt; n &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; x &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;as&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;int&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;}&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-groovy" data-lang="groovy"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// WRONG: Wrong generic type assumption
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;List&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;&amp;lt;&lt;/span&gt;Integer&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;&amp;gt;&lt;/span&gt; numbers &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;[&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;1&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;,&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;2&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;,&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;3&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;]&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;numbers&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;add&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;(&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;four&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;)&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// may fail at runtime with ClassCastException
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// CORRECT: Use proper typing
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;List&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;&amp;lt;&lt;/span&gt;Integer&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;&amp;gt;&lt;/span&gt; numbers &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;[&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;1&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;,&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;2&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;,&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;3&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;]&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;numbers&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;add&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;(&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;4&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;)&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// correct
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h2 id="examples"&gt;Examples&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-groovy" data-lang="groovy"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// Example 1: String to Integer
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;def&lt;/span&gt; s &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;hello&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;int&lt;/span&gt; n &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; s &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;as&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;int&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// ClassCastException
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// Example 2: Wrong collection type
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;def&lt;/span&gt; list &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;[&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;1&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;,&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;2&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;,&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;3&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;]&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;as&lt;/span&gt; ArrayList
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;list&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;add&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;(&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;four&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;)&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// ClassCastException when iterating
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// Example 3: Interface cast
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;class&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;Dog&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;{&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;void&lt;/span&gt; bark&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;()&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;{}&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;}&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;def&lt;/span&gt; animal &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;new&lt;/span&gt; Dog&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;()&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;def&lt;/span&gt; runnable &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; animal &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;as&lt;/span&gt; Runnable &lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// ClassCastException
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h2 id="related-errors"&gt;Related Errors&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/groovy/null-pointer5"&gt;NullPointerException&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/groovy/missing-method"&gt;MissingMethodException: No signature of method&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;</description></item><item><title>ClassCastException</title><link>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/scala/class-cast/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/scala/class-cast/</guid><description>&lt;h2 id="what-this-error-means"&gt;What This Error Means&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;A &lt;code&gt;ClassCastException&lt;/code&gt; is thrown when you try to cast an object to a type that it isn&amp;rsquo;t. This happens with explicit &lt;code&gt;asInstanceOf&lt;/code&gt; calls or when the compiler infers the wrong type due to type erasure.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id="common-causes"&gt;Common Causes&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Explicit cast with &lt;code&gt;asInstanceOf&lt;/code&gt; to wrong type&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Type erasure in generic collections&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Incorrect assumption about collection element types&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Java interop returning unexpected types&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h2 id="how-to-fix"&gt;How to Fix&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-scala" data-lang="scala"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// WRONG: Unsafe cast
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;val&lt;/span&gt; x&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;:&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;Any&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;hello&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;val&lt;/span&gt; n&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;:&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;Int&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; x&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;asInstanceOf&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;[&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;Int&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;]&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// ClassCastException
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// CORRECT: Use pattern matching or isInstanceOf check
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;val&lt;/span&gt; x&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;:&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;Any&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;hello&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;x &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;match&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;{&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;case&lt;/span&gt; n&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;:&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;Int&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&amp;gt;&lt;/span&gt; println&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;(&lt;/span&gt;n&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;)&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;case&lt;/span&gt; s&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;:&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;String&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&amp;gt;&lt;/span&gt; println&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;(&lt;/span&gt;s&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;)&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;}&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-scala" data-lang="scala"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// WRONG: Type erasure issue
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;val&lt;/span&gt; list&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;:&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;List&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;[&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;Any&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;]&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;List&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;(&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;1&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;,&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;two&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;,&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;3.0&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;)&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;val&lt;/span&gt; strings&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;:&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;List&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;[&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;String&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;]&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; list&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;asInstanceOf&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;[&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;List&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;[&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;String&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;]]&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// ClassCastException
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// CORRECT: Use collect or filter
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;val&lt;/span&gt; strings&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;:&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;List&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;[&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;String&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;]&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; list&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;collect &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;{&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;case&lt;/span&gt; s&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;:&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;String&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&amp;gt;&lt;/span&gt; s &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;}&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h2 id="examples"&gt;Examples&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-scala" data-lang="scala"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// Example 1: Direct cast
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;val&lt;/span&gt; obj&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;:&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;Any&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;hello&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;val&lt;/span&gt; num &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; obj&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;asInstanceOf&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;[&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;Int&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;]&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// ClassCastException
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// Example 2: Generic type erasure
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;val&lt;/span&gt; map &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;Map&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;(&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;a&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;-&amp;gt;&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;List&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;(&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;1&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;,&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;2&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;))&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;val&lt;/span&gt; wrong &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; map&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;asInstanceOf&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;[&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;Map&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;[&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;String&lt;/span&gt;, &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;List&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;[&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;String&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;]]]&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// may fail
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// Example 3: Java interop
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;import&lt;/span&gt; java.util.Collections
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;val&lt;/span&gt; javaList &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;Collections&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;emptyList&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;[&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;String&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;]()&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;val&lt;/span&gt; scalaList &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; javaList&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;asInstanceOf&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;[&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;List&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;[&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;String&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;]]&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// ClassCastException
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h2 id="related-errors"&gt;Related Errors&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/scala/null-pointer6"&gt;NullPointerException&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/scala/match-error4"&gt;MatchError&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;</description></item><item><title>[Solution] Java ClassCastException — Type Casting Fix</title><link>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/java/classcastexception/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/java/classcastexception/</guid><description>&lt;h1 id="classcastexception--type-casting-fix"&gt;ClassCastException — Type Casting Fix&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;A &lt;code&gt;ClassCastException&lt;/code&gt; is thrown when you attempt to cast an object to a type that it is not an instance of. This is one of the most common runtime exceptions in Java, especially when working with collections, generics, and reflection.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id="description"&gt;Description&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Java&amp;rsquo;s type system enforces casting rules at runtime. When you explicitly cast an object and the actual runtime type doesn&amp;rsquo;t match, the JVM throws a &lt;code&gt;ClassCastException&lt;/code&gt;. Common variants:&lt;/p&gt;</description></item></channel></rss>